598
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:21,560
Okay.

599
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:22,680
Khun Paga, right?

600
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:23,560
Yes.

601
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:24,880
Talk to you later.

602
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:27,840
Hey,

603
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:29,160
it his first day.

604
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:30,800
You sent him to the queen mum

605
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:33,080
He just needs to hand the document to her.

606
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:34,920
P’John

607
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:37,200
Whose drink are you having?

608
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,160
This?

609
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:40,000
I don’t know.

610
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,920
I found it in the fridge

611
00:34:44,640 --> 00:34:46,400
It’s mine.

612
00:34:46,640 --> 00:34:47,760
It’s yours?

613
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:51,800
let say I’ll buy it back to you.

614
00:34:52,120 --> 00:34:52,680
Okay.

615
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:53,440
Are we good?

616
00:34:53,640 --> 00:34:54,320
Yes

617
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:10,760
Yes, Okay.

618
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:12,200
You can do it.

619
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:14,480
Uh, excuse me.

620
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:18,920
Do you know where is Khun Paga’s table?

621
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,600
I’m Khun Paga.

622
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:28,440
All right.

623
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:31,240
Khun Earth asked me to hand this document to you.

624
00:35:32,760 --> 00:35:33,640
You work here.

625
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,120
How come you don’t know me?

626
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:37,240
Which department are you?

627
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,560
Procurement Department.

628
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:41,720
You are a new employee, right?

629
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:47,000
A new employee must firstly introduce himself to the senior employee.

630
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:49,960
Not just drop the document and leave like this!

631
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,480
Don’t you know this basic manner?

632
00:35:55,560 --> 00:35:57,000
I’m sorry, Khun Paga.

633
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:59,040
My name is Arthit.

634
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:01,280
If you’ll excuse, I have to leave now

635
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:02,800
Wait.

636
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:05,720
You must wait for me to review this document first.

637
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:09,280
If there’s any error, it can get amended right away

638
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:11,240
Seriously, young people these days

639
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:12,680
are no good.

640
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,200
Follow me.

641
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:33,720
How’d it go, newbie?

642
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,280
Is every all right?

643
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,160
Yes.

644
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:39,080
Khun Paga is a bit strict.

645
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:42,120
But actually she’s a nice person.

646
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:44,880
I see

647
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:49,400
Everyone, listen.

648
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:51,400
You probably got to know Arthit already.

649
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,800
He’s a new employee in our department

650
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:56,880
Well, we got a mix-up this morning

651
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:02,720
Why don’t you introduce yourself to your colleagues again officially?

652
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:05,560
Go ahead.

653
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,040
Yes.

654
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:10,200
Sawasdee krap, all of you.

655
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,880
My name is Arthit.

656
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:16,080
I graduated from SFU with a degree in engineering

657
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,400
Nice to meet you all

658
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:20,880
I got transferred to take a position here from the Production Department.

659
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:24,600
Arthit, is your nickname Arthit too?

660
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:26,480
No,

661
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:29,280
but my friends like to call me with my real name.

662
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:30,840
Since you all know him.

663
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:33,000
Let’s have a welcome dinner this evening.

664
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:35,360
Well, we….

665
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:37,240
My treat.

666
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:40,880
…we can’t wait to eat with Arthit

667
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:42,400
What should we have?

668
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:43,840
How about Shabu?

669
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:45,120
Som-O.

670
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:47,800
You are fast in this matter.

671
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,080
All right, then

672
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:52,080
Give me 30 minutes.

673
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:54,000
If you don’t mind

674
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:55,360
No problem.

675
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,240
Here.

676
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:10,600
Enough, P’John

677
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:13,000
You can tell me if you want something

678
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:14,600
I grab it for you.

679
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:15,880
He can get it himself.

680
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:17,280
Please have a seat, P’Danai.

681
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:20,400
I’m really sorry to have kept you waiting for me

682
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:21,840
I was on the phone with my son.

683
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:24,360
He vented about his university

684
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:28,200
Is it okay if you don’t go have an have dinner with your family?

685
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:29,440
It’s okay now.

686
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:32,280
My son has moved out and stayed in a dorm near his campus.

687
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:36,080
It’s good for him. He will experience a lot of things his own.

688
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:36,920
Yes, I agree.

689
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:40,840
That’s why you take us out for dinner.

690
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:41,960
The thing is

691
00:38:42,080 --> 00:38:44,760
it’s been a while that we get to welcome a new employee

692
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:47,960
Also, you all have been working really hard

693
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:52,240
So I want to reward you for your hard work.

694
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:54,920
What are you talking about?

695
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:58,560
Our work is not that hard, right?

696
00:38:58,640 --> 00:39:00,600
You are scaring N’Arthit

697
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:02,840
N’Arthit

698
00:39:03,160 --> 00:39:05,400
have you had someone to cook for you yet?

699
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:07,920
I’m good at cooking, you know?

700
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:12,200
Well, I…

701
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,480
Hey, P’John.

702
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:15,400
That’s pork is mine.

703
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:16,080
What?

704
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,760
I saw it was in the pot for a while.

705
00:39:17,920 --> 00:39:19,160
I don’t want it to get more shrunken.

706
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,200
It’s not gonna shrunken.

707
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:23,760
I can boil you a new one

708
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:26,880
I want lean pork.

709
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:31,280
Thank you.

710
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,480
See you tomorrow morning.

711
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:33,800
Please take care.

712
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:35,240
Want to go to a bar together, Som-O?

713
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:39,680
Hello, Kongpob?

714
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:40,680
How’d it go?

715
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:42,040
Your gathering activity was over?

716
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:43,720
It was over a while ago.

717
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:46,000
I’m on my way to my dorm.

718
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:46,960
What about you?

719
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:47,720
Are you home yet?

720
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:49,720
Not yet.

721
00:39:50,040 --> 00:39:52,080
I just had dinner with my colleagues

722
00:39:52,720 --> 00:39:55,920
How was your first day in the Procurement Department?

723
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,280
Well…

724
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:59,520
there were some hectic moments

725
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,840
I feel strange.

726
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:06,760
I feel like I’m a freshman once again and got scolded by seniors.

727
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,080
What about you?

728
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:09,080
How is it going?

729
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:11,200
Are the initiation activities going all right?

730
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:13,480
The freshmen are fully cooperative.

731
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:16,520
